TypeSignature.Value: .class public auto ansi sealed Key extends System.Enum

Docs.summary: Specifies the possible key values on a keyboard.

remarks.format: ## Remarks Information pertaining to key input can be obtained in several different ways in WPF. Key-related events, such as <xref:System.Windows.UIElement.KeyDown> and <xref:System.Windows.UIElement.KeyUp>, provide key state information through the <xref:System.Windows.Input.KeyEventArgs> object that is passed to the event handler. Key state information can also be obtained through the static methods on the <xref:System.Windows.Input.Keyboard> class, such as <xref:System.Windows.Input.Keyboard.IsKeyUp%2A> and <xref:System.Windows.Input.Keyboard.GetKeyStates%2A>. The <xref:System.Windows.Input.Keyboard> class reports the current state of the keyboard.
